post_text: At approximately 3 p.m. today, Weedsport learned that the New York State Public High School Athletic Association was indefinitely postponing its winter championships which includes the boys’ basketball tournament. While this is an unfortunate situation, it in no way diminishes the memorable and historic season the Weedsport Boys’ Basketball team has put together with the support of our school community. While a possible opportunity to capture a State championship may be denied, we can still be proud of the fact that the squad was crowned Section III champions for the first time in 40 years.

post_text:
Tomorrow is the big day. Both the boys’ and girls’ basketball teams play in the finals of the Section 3 tournament at Onondaga Community College.The girls will play Cooperstown at 11 a.m. at Allyn Hall and the boys will also play Cooperstown at 2 p.m. at the SRC Arena. Admission is $8 per person and covers both games.
Can’t make it to the games on Saturday? You can stream them for as little as $10.99 per month using the NFHS Network. Follow the link below
https://www.nfhsnetwork.com/.
Once you pay the fee search basketball in NYS and both games this weekend will be streamed live. You will also have access to other playoff games and other events taking place in NYS.

post_text:
GRADUATES OF DISTINCTION NOMINATIONS SOUGHT
The Weedsport Central School District Board of Education has established a Graduates of Distinction program to honor Weedsport Central School District graduates for lifetime achievement. Honorees, living or deceased, will be mature adults who are/were exemplary citizens having distinguished themselves through their communities, professions, or careers. This may include service to humanity, exceptional career achievement, or a lifetime of accomplishment in many areas. No person shall be eligible for this honor until at least 10 years following the date of graduation from Weedsport Central School District. The recipients will be permanently honored at Weedsport Central School and will be publicly recognized.
The nomination packets can be obtained by either visiting the District Office and requesting such or contacting the District Office at 315-834-6637 for a mailing. The closing date for submission of the nomination packets will be March 1 of each year. The honorees will be publicly recognized at the Weedsport Alumni Banquet in June.

post_text:
Congratulations to the 1978-79 Weedsport varsity girls’ basketball team which was just inducted into the Weedsport Sports Hall of Fame. The team – which featured a 15-3 record – was the first girls’ basketball team at Weedsport to win a Sectional title. The members of the team included: Chere Clark, Laurie Francisco, Mary Simons, Wendi Snook, Donna Upfold, Theresa D’Attilio, Margaret Kreplin, Laureen Martin, Kathy Streeter, and Elaine Riley. The team was coached by Mark Dunn.
Read more below!
